data.name: label17.Text
data.value:
WinPaletter has a feature that enables user to change Windows theme (visual styles).
- There was an obstacle: modified, patched, or unsigned visual styles cannot be applied to Windows.
- This is solvable by using SecureUxTheme. It requires a setup then a Windows restart.

data.name: label13.Text
data.value:
- Themes are automatically backed up before applying a new theme or making changes to a single Windows aspect.
- You can also back up themes when opening WinPaletter or before opening a new theme file. These options are disabled by default and can be enabled in Settings > Themes backup.

data.name: label16.Text
data.value:
- If you are not using other third-party tools and have a standard Windows setup, you can ignore this alert.
- Remember that you can always restore a theme from backups if you've made modifications to your Windows setup with preferences you don't like.

data.name: label14.Text
data.value: 1. Back up third-party tool settings. 2. Back up the WinPaletter theme file. 3. Create a Windows restore point (optional). 4. Use WinPaletter on Windows without any mods (avoid other third-party tools) (optional). 5. Do some tests in a virtual machine (optional). 6. If you insist on using another third-party tool, don't use WinPaletter's Windows Effects (disable it). 7. Be cautious when using Display Fusion and WinPaletter's Windows Switcher (Alt+Tab appearance), as there might be occasional issues (though unlikely).
